**ESOPs (Employee Stock Options)** are taxed in two stages in India: (1) At exercise: the difference between FMV and exercise price is treated as perquisite income and taxed at slab rate; (2) At sale: the difference between sale price and FMV on exercise date is taxed as capital gains (LTCG at 12.5% if held 12+ months, STCG at 20% otherwise). This calculator handles both stages.
